Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the State University of New York in Buffalo, praising the work being done to address the climate crisis and emphasizing the importance of investing in clean energy and environmental justice. She highlighted the impact of the climate crisis on young people and stressed the need for urgent action. Harris discussed the administration's efforts to boost clean energy production, including investing in wind turbines and solar farms, as well as providing financial support for families to install solar panels and transition to electric vehicles. She also emphasized the importance of addressing equity in climate solutions, particularly for marginalized communities. Harris stated that the nation is on track to meet its emissions reduction goals but acknowledged that more work needs to be done. She expressed gratitude to the students and professionals working to address the climate crisis and encouraged them to continue their efforts.